@EdisonXu We changed tablesorter.js's master from christianbach to Mottie.

original source code (current master) is https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/blob/master/js/jquery.tablesorter.js

It already replaces currency to unicode representation, so I said there seems to no problem.

```
ts.addParser({
        id: "currency",
        is: function(s) {
            return (/^\(?\d+[\u00a3$\u20ac\u00a4\u00a5\u00a2?.]|[\u00a3$\u20ac\u00a4\u00a5\u00a2?.]\d+\)?$/).test((s || '').replace(/[+\-,. ]/g,'')); // £$€¤¥¢
        },
        format: function(s, table) {
            var n = ts.formatFloat((s || '').replace(/[^\w,. \-()]/g, ""), table);
            return s && typeof n === 'number' ? n : s ? $.trim( s && table.config.ignoreCase ? s.toLocaleLowerCase() : s ) : s;
        },
        type: "numeric"
    });
```

We use jquery.tablesorter.min.js, so currency comment is removed.

